dataDictionary.Title: PDS4 Data Dictionary
dataDictionary.Description: This document is a dump of the contents of the PDS4 Data Dictionary

class.title: USER
class.description: The root class.

class.title: Color_Display_Settings
class.description: The Color_Display_Settings class provides guidance to data users on how to display a multi-banded Array object on a color-capable display device.

class.title: Display_Direction
class.description: The Display_Direction class specifies how two of the dimensions of an Array object should be displayed in the vertical (line) and horizontal (sample) dimensions of a display device.

class.title: Display_Settings
class.description: The Display_Settings class contains one or more classes describing how data should be displayed on a display device.

class.title: Movie_Display_Settings
class.description: The Movie_Display_Settings class provides default values for the display of a multi-banded Array using a software application capable of displaying video content.

class.title: Acceleration_Vector_Cartesian_Base
class.description: The Acceleration_Vector_Cartesian_Base is a three dimensional, rectangular coordinates vector. Uses units of linear acceleration. The included attributes are not sufficient to identify the endpoints of the vector.

class.title: Acceleration_Vector_Cartesian_Extended_Base
class.description: The Acceleration_Vector_Cartesian_Extended_Base is a three dimensional, rectangular coordinates vector. Uses units of linear acceleration. The included attributes are not sufficient to identify the endpoints of the vector. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Acceleration_Vector_Cartesian_Generic
class.description: Acceleration_Vector_Cartesian_Generic is a three dimensional, rectangular coordinates vector. Uses units of linear acceleration. Includes attributes to identify the endpoints of the vector. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Articulation_Device_Parameters
class.description: The Articulation_Device_Parameters class contains those attributes and sub-classes that describe an articulation device. An articulation device is anything that can move independently of the spacecraft to which it is attached. Examples include mast heads, wheel bogies, arms, filter wheel, scan platforms.

class.title: Axis_Vector
class.description: The Axis_Vector describes the axis of the camera, defined as the normal to the image plane.

class.title: Body_Identification_Base
class.description: The Body_Identification_Base class provides multiple attributes which can be used to identify a physical object (spacecraft, planet instrument, transmitter, system barycenter, etc.). At least one must be used.

class.title: CAHVORE_Model
class.description: A third model, CAHVORE, describes more general cameras including those with fisheye or otherwise wide field of view lenses. An additional vector, E, describes the apparent motion of the camera entrance pupil. (Taken from Camera Response Simulation for Planetary Exploration, by Dr. Richard Madison, Marc Pomerantz, and Dr. Abhinandan Jain, http://trs-new.jpl.nasa.gov/dspace/bitstream/2014/37771/1/05-1692.pdf)

class.title: CAHVOR_Model
class.description: The CAHVOR model describes a camera with radial lens distortion about the lens axis. In addition to the CAHV parameters, it includes 3-vectors O and R. Vector O is the optical axis of the lens, slightly different from vector A due to imperfect lens mounting. A ray from a point in space, passing through the pinhole, bends at the pinhole according to a function of the angle between the ray and optical axis O. The function is a polynomial whose coefficients are stored in vector R. (Taken from Camera Response Simulation for Planetary Exploration, by Dr. Richard Madison, Marc Pomerantz, and Dr. Abhinandan Jain, http://trs-new.jpl.nasa.gov/dspace/bitstream/2014/37771/1/05-1692.pdf)

class.title: CAHV_Model
class.description: The CAHV camera model is equivalent to the standard linear photogrammetric model for a pinhole camera, It is useful for very small field of view cameras and as a building block for more complex camera models. The CAHV model consists of four 3-vectors: C, A, H, and V. Vector C gives the location of the pinhole. Vector A gives the camera axis, defined as the normal to the image plane. Vector H encodes the horizontal axis of the image plane (H'), the coor- dinate (Hc) of the image column at the optical center of the image plane, and the horizontal focal length (Hs) of the camera, in pixels. Vector V encodes corresponding information (V', Vc, Vs) in the vertical direction. The angle (theta) between horizontal and vertical vectors H' and V' is about 90 degrees. (Taken from Camera Response Simulation for Planetary Exploration, by Dr. Richard Madison, Marc Pomerantz, and Dr. Abhinandan Jain, http://trs-new.jpl.nasa.gov/dspace/bitstream/2014/37771/1/05-1692.pdf)

class.title: Camera_Model_Parameters
class.description: A camera model describes the mathematical relationship between the coordinates of a point in 3-dimensional space and its projection onto a 2-dimensional image plane. There are numerous types of camera models, only two of which are currently implemented.

class.title: Center_Vector
class.description: The Center_Vector describes the location of the pinhole of a camera.

class.title: Central_Body_Identification
class.description: The Central_Body_Identification class uniquely identifies the body which is the central body associated with an observation (e.g., Saturn for Saturn system observations).

class.title: Central_Body_To_Spacecraft_Position_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: The Central_Body_To_Spacecraft_Position_Vector_Cartesian is a linear, rectangular coordinates vector from the center of mass of the central body (e.g., planet) to the spacecraft. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Central_Body_To_Spacecraft_Position_Vector_Planetocentric
class.description: The Central_Body_To_Spacecraft_Position_Vector_Planetocentric is a spherical position vector in Planetocentric coordinates. It extends from the center of mass of the central body (e.g., planet) to the spacecraft. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Central_Body_To_Target_Position_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: The Central_Body_To_Target_Position_Vector_Cartesian is a linear, rectangular coordinates vector from the center of mass of the central body (e.g., planet) to the target specified in the parent Geometry_Orbiter class. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Central_Body_To_Target_Position_Vector_Planetocentric
class.description: The Central_Body_To_Target_Position_Vector_Planetocentric is a spherical position vector in Planetocentric coordinates. It extends from the center of mass of the central body (e.g., planet) to the target specified in the parent Geometry_Orbiter class. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Coordinate_Space_Definition
class.description: The Coordinate_Space classes are typically used for lander/rover geometry while the Coordinate_System construction is used for orbiter/flyby geometry.

class.title: Coordinate_Space_Identification
class.description: The Coordinate_Space_Identification class uniquely identifies a coordinate space (i.e., reference frame + position) with respect to which the values of the attributes in the containing class are defined.

class.title: Coordinate_Space_Index
class.description: Identifies a coordinate space using an index value given in an identified list.

class.title: Coordinate_Space_Indexed
class.description: The Coordinate_Space_Indexed class contains the attributes and classes identifying the indexed coordinate space.

class.title: Coordinate_Space_SPICE
class.description: Identifies a coordinate space using SPICE names for the frame and origin.

class.title: Coordinate_System_Identification
class.description: The Coordinate_System_Identification class fully describes a coordinate system. This class is typically used for orbiter/flyby geometry while the Coordinate_Space construction is used for lander/rover geometry. Coordinate_System_Identification provides the reference frame, coordinate system type (cartesian, planetocentric, etc.), origin, and the instantiation time of the system when appropriate. The instantiation time (coordinate_system_time) is used when a rotating frame has been 'frozen' at a particular epoch. Instantiation time is not needed for inertial or rotating frames.

class.title: Coordinate_System_Origin_Identification
class.description: The Coordinate_System_Origin_Identification class uniquely identifies the body that is the origin of a coordinate system. Note that the origin of coordinate system does not necessarily correspond to either end point of a vector.

class.title: Derived_Geometry
class.description: The Derived_Geometry class is a container for surface based observations (lander or rover). It is used to provide some geometric quantities relative to a specific Reference Coordinate Space.

class.title: Device_Angle
class.description: The Device_Angle class is a container for the set of angles between the various components or devices of the spacecraft.

class.title: Device_Angle_Index
class.description: The Device_Angle_Index class is a container for one angle between two parts or components of a device.

class.title: Device_Component_State
class.description: The Device_Component_State class is a container for the states of the various components of the articulation device.

class.title: Device_Component_State_Index
class.description: The Device_Component_State_Index class is a container for one state of a component of the articulation device.

class.title: Device_Gravity_Vector
class.description: The Device_Gravity_Vector class specifies the direction and magnitude of an external force acting on the articulation device, in the spacecraft's coordinate system, at the time the pose was computed.

class.title: Device_Motor_Counts
class.description: The Device_Motor_Counts class is a container for the classes that describe the motor step count information for device components.

class.title: Device_Motor_Counts_Index
class.description: The Device_Motor_Counts_Index class is a container for the attributes that describe the motor step count information for a single motor on a device.

class.title: Device_Temperature
class.description: The Device_Temperature class is a container for all available device temperatures of an articulated device and/or part(s) of a device.

class.title: Device_Temperature_Index
class.description: The Device_Temperature_Index class specifies the attributes describing the temperature of one device or some part of a device.

class.title: Distance_Generic
class.description: The distance between the two objects, both of which must be specified.

class.title: Distances
class.description: The Distances class is a container class for distances.

class.title: Earth_To_Central_Body_Position_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: The Earth_To_Central_Body_Position_Vector_Cartesian is a linear, rectangular coordinates vector from the Earth to the central body (e.g., planet). While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Earth_To_Spacecraft_Position_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: The Earth_To_Spacecraft_Position_Vector_Cartesian is a linear, rectangular coordinates vector from the Earth to the spacecraft. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Earth_To_Target_Position_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: The Earth_To_Target_Position_Vector_Cartesian is a linear, rectangular coordinates vector from the Earth to the target specified in the parent Geometry_Orbiter class. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Entrance_Vector
class.description: The Entrance_Vector describes the location of the entrance pupil of a camera.

class.title: Footprint_Vertices
class.description: The Footprint_Vertices class provides a set of associations between pixels and their projections on the target. The pixels should be choose to be the vertices of a polygon, plotted sequenually in a the direction.

class.title: Frame_Identification_Base
class.description: The Frame_Identification_Base class provides multiple attributes which can be used to identify a reference frame. At least one must be used.

class.title: Generic_Vectors
class.description: The Generic_Vectors class is a container class for all of the build your own vector templates.

class.title: Geometry
class.description: The Geometry class is a container for all geometric information in the label.

class.title: Geometry_Lander
class.description: The Geometry_Lander class is a container for all geometric information in the label relating to a landed spacecraft, including rovers.

class.title: Geometry_Orbiter
class.description: The Geometry_Orbiter class is a container for geometric information (positions, velocities, orientations, etc.) relevant to orbiter or flyby spacecraft observations. Specify a value for Reference_Frame_Identification at this level only when a single reference frame is used in the contained classes. If more that one reference frame is used, specify them in the contained classes. If any of the contained classes or attributes have central body, and or target in the class or attribute name (e.g., spacecraft_to_central_body_distance, Spacecraft_To_Target_Position_Vector_Planetocentric), then the central body and or target must be identified in this class. If more than one target or central body need to be identified to fully describe the data, use multiple instances of the Geometry_Orbiter class. Do not use Coordinate_System at this level if more than one coordinate system is used in the contained classes. If more than one coordinate system is used, specify Coordinate_System in each of the subordinate classes where it is appropriate.

class.title: Horizontal_Vector
class.description: The Horizontal_Vector encodes the horizontal axis of the image plane (H'), the coordinate (Hc) of the image column at the optical center of the image plane, and the horizontal focal length (Hs) of the camera, in pixels.

class.title: Illumination_FOV_Range_Values
class.description: The Illumination_FOV_Range_Values class contains attributes providing illumination parameters as minimum/maximum pairs for either the field of view or the portion in the FoV of the target specified in the parent Geometry_Orbiter class.

class.title: Illumination_Geometry
class.description: The Illumination_Geometry class contains two optional classes used to describing the field of view lighting.

class.title: Illumination_Single_Values
class.description: The Illumination_Single_Values class contains attributes providing illumination parameters at a single location in the field of view. If reference_location is used, and indicates a point on a target, the target must be the one specified in the parent Geometry_Orbiter class.

class.title: Image_Display_Geometry
class.description: Image_Display_Geometry class provides an unambiguous description of the orientation of the image contents. Given an image, displayed as described by the Display_Direction class, any one of the Object_Orientation_* classes should allow unambiguous orientation of the contents of the image. The use of disp:Display_Direction is optional, but must be given either here or in the Display Discipline Area of the label. The Object_Orientation_North_East class is typically used for instruments for which the entire field of view is a portion of the target surface (e.g., instruments on Mars orbital spacecraft); otherwise use Object_Orientation_RA_Dec (e.g., flyby missions, missions with orbit radii much larger than the target radius such as Voyager or Cassini). At least one of these must be used. The three _Identification classes used here are Central_Body (e.g., Saturn if you are using Planetocentric or planetographic coordinates in the Saturn system); Body is typically used in lieu of Central_Body when the coordinates are based on a comet, asteroid, KBO, or satellite; Target when the described object in the FoV is not the Central_Body or Body. For example giving the orientation of the pole of Enceladus in Saturn Planetocentric coordinates, Central_Body = Saturn, Target = Enceladus. Bottom line: put in enough information so someone else can figure out the orientation of the field of view.

class.title: List_Index_Angle
class.description: Used when the list values are angles.

class.title: List_Index_Base
class.description: The List_Index class is a private (i.e., abstract) class designed to enable the use of indexed lists. The minimum requirement is at least one of sequence number, name or "id", plus the set of values themselves.

class.title: List_Index_Length
class.description: Used when the list values are lengths.

class.title: List_Index_No_Units
class.description: Used when the list values have no units.

class.title: List_Index_Temperature
class.description: Used when the list values are temperatures.

class.title: List_Index_Text
class.description: Used when the list values are strings.

class.title: Motion_Counter
class.description: The Motion_Counter class provides a set of integers which describe a (potentially) unique location (position / orientation) for a rover or other movable object. Each time an event occurs that results in a movement, a new motion counter value is created. This includes intentional motion due to drive commands, as well as potential motion due to other articulating devices, such as arms or antennae. This motion counter (or part of it) is used as a reference to define instances of coordinate systems which can move such as SITE or ROVER frames. The motion counter is defined in a mission-specific manner. Although the original intent was to have incrementing indices (e.g., MER), the motion counter could also contain any integer values which conform to the above definition, such as time or spacecraft clock values.

class.title: Motion_Counter_Index
class.description: The Motion_Counter_Index class identifies and populates one element of a Motion_Counter list. The class should be repeated for each element of the list.

class.title: Object_Orientation_Clock_Angles
class.description: The Object_Orientation_Clock_Angles class provides several clock angles which can be used to describe the orientation of the field of view with respect to various external references such as Celestial or Equatorial North.

class.title: Object_Orientation_North_East
class.description: The Object_Orientation_North_East class provides the parameters needed to describe the orientation of an external coordinate system relative to the image coordinate frame as described by the Image_Orientation class.

class.title: Object_Orientation_RA_Dec
class.description: The Object_Orientation_RA_Dec class provides the parameters needed to describe the orientation of the celestial reference frame relative to the image coordinate frame as described by the Image_Orientation class.

class.title: Observer_Identification
class.description: Within the Geometry dictionary context, an "Observer" is the body on the "from" end of a vector, or other translation through space.

class.title: Optical_Terms
class.description: The Optical_Terms provides the optical axis coefficients used for lens-distortion correction when the distortion is radial.

class.title: Origin_Offset_Vector
class.description: The Origin_Offset_Vector class contains attributes that specify the offset from the reference coordinate system's origin to the origin of the coordinate system. It is the location of the current system's origin as measured in the reference system.

class.title: Pixel_Dimensions
class.description: The Pixel_Dimensions class contains information regarding pixel size.

class.title: Pixel_Intercept
class.description: The Pixel_Intercept class provides the latitude and longitude on the surface of the target for the projection of the specificed pixel. The pixel is specfied using either reference_pixel_location or Reference_Pixel. Although each of these is optional, one must be used.

class.title: Pixel_Size_Projected
class.description: The Pixel_Size_Projected class gives the size, in units of length (e.g., kilometers) of the projection of a pixel onto the surface of the target which is specified in the parent Geometry_Orbiter class. The reference_location attribute is used to identify the specific point on the target.

class.title: Polynomial_Coefficients_1
class.description: The Polynomial_Coefficients_1 class provides a one polynomial coefficient.

class.title: Polynomial_Coefficients_2
class.description: The Polynomial_Coefficients_2 class provides two polynomial coefficients.

class.title: Polynomial_Coefficients_3
class.description: The Polynomial_Coefficients_3 class provides three polynomial coefficients.

class.title: Position_Vector_Cartesian_Base
class.description: The Position_Vector_Cartesian_Base is a three dimensional, rectangular coordinates vector. Uses units of length. The included attributes are not sufficient to identify the endpoints of the vector.

class.title: Position_Vector_Cartesian_Extended_Base
class.description: The Position_Vector_Cartesian_Extended_Base is a three dimensional, rectangular coordinates vector. Uses units of length. The included attributes are not sufficient to identify the endpoints of the vector. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Position_Vector_Cartesian_Generic
class.description: Position_Vector_Cartesian_Generic is a three dimensional, rectangular coordinates vector. Uses units of length. Includes attributes to identify the endpoints of the vector. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Position_Vector_Planetocentric_Base
class.description: The Position_Vector_Planetocentric_Base is a three dimensional spherical vector (radius, longitude, latitude) with the angular coordinates defined to be consistent with the Planetocentric coordinate system. Uses linear units for the radius dimension, and angular units for the other two dimensions. The included attributes are not sufficient to identify the endpoints of the vector.

class.title: Position_Vector_Planetocentric_Extended_Base
class.description: The Position_Vector_Planetocentric_Extended_Base is a three dimensional spherical vector (radius, longitude, latitude) with the angular coordinates defined to be consistent with the Planetocentric coordinate system. Uses linear units for the radius dimension, and angular units for the other two dimensions. The included attributes are not sufficient to identify the endpoints of the vector. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Position_Vector_Planetocentric_Generic
class.description: The Position_Vector_Planetocentric_Generic is a three dimensional spherical vector (radius, longitude, latitude) with the angular coordinates defined to be consistent with the Planetocentric coordinate system. Uses linear units for the radius dimension, and angular units for the other two dimensions. Includes attributes to identify the endpoints of the vector. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Present_Coordinate_Space
class.description: The Present_Coordinate_Space class includes the attributes that identifies the spacecraft's present coordinate space.

class.title: Quaternion_1
class.description: Quaternion_1 provides the four elements of a quaternion and its direction of rotation.

class.title: Quaternion_2
class.description: Quaternion_2 provides the four elements of a quaternion and identifies the initial (Rotate_From)and final (Rotate_To) frames of the rotation.

class.title: Quaternion_Base
class.description: The Quaternion_Base class defines a quaternion that represents rotation between two right-handed reference frames. In this dictionary, quaternions are always constructed so that the application of the quaternion describes the rotation of one frame to a second frame. The two frames and the direction of rotation must be identified unambiguously in the enclosing classes. Quaternions are expressed as a set of four numbers in the order (qcos, qsin1, qsin2, qsin3), where qcos = cos(theta/2) and qsin(n) = sin(theta/2)*a(n). Theta is the angle of rotation and a is the unit vector (x,y,z) around which the rotation occurs. A document providing the full mathematical basis for this construction, along with examples, and a summary of common pitfalls, is in preparation. The current version can be obtained by contacting the PDS Engineering Node. [mkg: When it is finished we'll ingest it into the registry and refer to it by LID]

class.title: Radial_Terms
class.description: The Radial_Terms class provides the radial lens distortion coefficients defined in the ground (object) coordinate system.

class.title: Reference_Coordinate_Space
class.description: The Reference_Coordinate_Space class includes the attributes that identify the reference coordinate space to be used in relation to the spacecraft's present coordinate space. The reference coordinate space is the space in which the present coordinate space is defined.

class.title: Reference_Frame_Identification
class.description: The Reference_Frame_Identification class is a base class for identifying reference frames. These are frames in the NAIF sense, i.e., three orthogonal axes with a specified orientation, but without a fixed origin.

class.title: Reference_Pixel
class.description: The Reference_Pixel class provides the pixel coordinates, line and sample, to which values in the containing class apply. Integer values indicate the center of the pixel. Sub-pixel values are permitted. For pixel_sample, the leading edge (left edge for sample increasing to the right) has a value 0.5 less than the integer value at the center, and the value for the trailing edge is the center integer value + 0.5. For pixel_line, the leading and trailing edges (top and bottom respectively for line increasing downward) again are -0.5 and +0.5 with respect to the center integer value.

class.title: Rotate_From
class.description: A quaternion rotates one reference frame to another reference frame. The Rotate_From class identifies the initial frame.

class.title: Rotate_To
class.description: A quaternion rotates a one reference frame to another reference frame. The Rotate_To class identifies the destination frame.

class.title: SPICE_Kernel_Files
class.description: The SPICE_Kernel_Files class provides references to the SPICE files used when calculating geometric values.

class.title: SPICE_Kernel_Identification
class.description: The SPICE_Kernel_Identification class optionally includes the SPICE kernel type and provides two alternatives for identifying the product: LIDVID using Internal_Reference, and the file name of the kernel file. Although optional, LIDVID should be given if one is available.

class.title: SSB_To_Central_Body_Position_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: The SSB_To_Central_Body_Position_Vector_Cartesian is a linear, rectangular coordinates vector from the Solar System Barycenter to the central body (e.g., planet). While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: SSB_To_Spacecraft_Position_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: The SSB_To_Spacecraft_Position_Vector_Cartesian is a linear, rectangular coordinates vector from the Solar System Barycenter to the spacecraft. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: SSB_To_Target_Position_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: The SSB_To_Target_Position_Vector_Cartesian is a linear, rectangular coordinates vector from the Solar System Barycenter to the target specified in the parent Geometry_Orbiter class. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Spacecraft_Relative_To_Central_Body_Velocity_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: The Spacecraft_Relative_To_Central_Body_Velocity_Vector_Cartesian is a velocity vector in rectangular coordinates that gives the velocity of the spacecraft with respect to the central body (e.g., planet). While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Spacecraft_Relative_To_Earth_Velocity_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: The Spacecraft_Relative_To_Earth_Velocity_Vector_Cartesian is a velocity vector in rectangular coordinates that gives the velocity of the spacecraft with respect to Earth. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Spacecraft_Relative_To_SSB_Velocity_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: The Spacecraft_Relative_To_SSB_Velocity_Vector_Cartesian is a velocity vector in rectangular coordinates that gives the velocity of the spacecraft with respect to the Solar System Barycenter. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Spacecraft_Relative_To_Sun_Velocity_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: Spacecraft_Relative_To_Sun_Velocity_Vector_Cartesian is a velocity vector in rectangular coordinates that gives the velocity of the spacecraft with respect to the center of the Sun. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Spacecraft_Relative_To_Target_Velocity_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: The Spacecraft_Relative_To_Target_Velocity_Vector_Cartesian is a velocity vector in rectangular coordinates that gives the velocity of the spacecraft with respect to the target specified in the parent Geometry_Orbiter class. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Spacecraft_Relative_To_Target_Velocity_Vector_Planetocentric
class.description: The Spacecraft_Relative_To_Target_Velocity_Vector_Planetocentric is a spherical velocity vector in Planetocentric coordinates that gives the velocity of the spacecraft with respect to the designated target. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Spacecraft_To_Target_Position_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: The Spacecraft_To_Target_Position_Vector_Cartesian is a linear, rectangular coordinates vector from the spacecraft to the target specified in the parent Geometry_Orbiter class. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Spacecraft_To_Target_Position_Vector_Planetocentric
class.description: The Spacecraft_To_Target_Position_Vector_Planetocentric is a spherical position vector in Planetocentric coordinates. It extends from the spacecraft to the target specified in the parent Geometry_Orbiter class.. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Specific_Cartesian_Vectors
class.description: The Specific_Cartesian_Vectors class is a container class for all cartesian vectors with pre-identified endpoints.

class.title: Specific_Planetocentric_Vectors
class.description: The Specific_Planetocentric_Vectors class is a container class for all planetocentric vectors with pre-identified endpoints.

class.title: Specific_Position_Vectors
class.description: The Specific_Position_Vectors class is a container class for all position vectors with pre-identified endpoints.

class.title: Specific_Velocity_Vectors
class.description: The Specific_Velocity_Vectors class is a container class for all velocity vectors with pre-identified endpoints.

class.title: Subordinate_Devices
class.description: The Subordinate_Devices class is a container for identifying the instruments mounted on the articulation device.

class.title: Sun_To_Central_Body_Position_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: The Sun_To_Central_Body_Position_Vector_Cartesian is a linear, rectangular coordinates vector from the Sun to the central body (e.g., planet). While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Sun_To_Spacecraft_Position_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: The Sun_To_Spacecraft_Position_Vector_Cartesian is a linear, rectangular coordinates vector from the Sun to the spacecraft. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Sun_To_Target_Position_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: The Sun_To_Target_Position_Vector_Cartesian is a linear, rectangular coordinates vector from the Sun to the target specified in the parent Geometry_Orbiter class. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Surface_Geometry
class.description: The Surface_Geometry class contains classes and attributes for various points of the surface of the target designated in the enclosing Geometry_Orbiter.

class.title: Target_Identification
class.description: Within the Geometry dictionary context, a "Target" is the body on the "to" end of a vector, or other translation through space.

class.title: Target_Relative_To_Central_Body_Velocity_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: The Target_Relative_To_Central_Body_Velocity_Vector_Cartesian is a velocity vector in rectangular coordinates that gives the velocity of the designated target with respect to the central body (e.g., planet). While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Target_Relative_To_Central_Body_Velocity_Vector_Planetocentric
class.description: The Target_Relative_To_Central_Body_Velocity_Vector_Planetocentric is a spherical velocity vector in Planetocentric coordinates that gives the velocity of the target with respect to the central body. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Target_Relative_To_Earth_Velocity_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: The Target_Relative_To_Earth_Velocity_Vector_Cartesian is a velocity vector in rectangular coordinates that gives the velocity of the designated target with respect to Earth. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Target_Relative_To_SSB_Velocity_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: The Target_Relative_To_SSB_Velocity_Vector_Cartesian is a velocity vector in rectangular coordinates that gives the velocity of the designated target with respect to the Solar System Barycenter. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Target_Relative_To_Spacecraft_Velocity_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: The Target_Relative_To_Spacecraft_Velocity_Vector_Cartesian is a velocity vector in rectangular coordinates that gives the velocity of the designated target with respect to the spacecraft. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Target_Relative_To_Spacecraft_Velocity_Vector_Planetocentric
class.description: The Target_Relative_To_Spacecraft_Velocity_Vector_Planetocentric is a spherical velocity vector in Planetocentric coordinates that gives the velocity of the target with respect to the spacecraft. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Target_Relative_To_Sun_Velocity_Vector_Cartesian
class.description: Target_Relative_To_Sun_Velocity_Vector_Cartesian is a velocity vector in rectangular coordinates that gives the velocity of the designated target with respect to the center of the sun. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Vector_Cartesian_No_Units
class.description: This is a generic vector in Cartesian space. The "x", "y", and "z" component have no units.

class.title: Vector_Cartesian_Pixel
class.description: This a Cartesian pixel vector generally used in camera models.

class.title: Vector_Cartesian_Unit
class.description: This is a generic unit vector in Cartesian space. The "x", "y", and "z" component have no units and are restricted to values between -1.0 and 1.0 inclusive. Further the length of the vector square root of the (sum of the squares of the components) must be 1.0.

class.title: Velocity_Vector_Cartesian_Base
class.description: The Velocity_Vector_Cartesian_Base is a three dimensional, rectangular coordinates vector. Uses units of linear velocity. The included attributes are not sufficient to identify the endpoints of the vector.

class.title: Velocity_Vector_Cartesian_Extended_Base
class.description: The Velocity_Vector_Cartesian_Extended_Base is a three dimensional, rectangular coordinates vector. Uses units of linear velocity. The included attributes are not sufficient to identify the endpoints of the vector. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Velocity_Vector_Cartesian_Generic
class.description: Velocity_Vector_Cartesian_Generic is a three dimensional, rectangular coordinates vector. Uses units of linear velocity. Includes attributes to identify the endpoints of the vector. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Velocity_Vector_Planetocentric_Base
class.description: The Velocity_Vector_Planetocentric_Base is a three dimensional spherical vector (radius, longitude, latitude) with the angular coordinates defined to be consistent with the Planetocentric coordinate system. Uses linear velocity units for the radius dimension, and angular velocity units for the other two dimensions. The included attributes are not sufficient to identify the endpoints of the vector.

class.title: Velocity_Vector_Planetocentric_Extended_Base
class.description: The Velocity_Vector_Planetocentric_Extended_Base is a three dimensional spherical vector (radius, longitude, latitude) with the angular coordinates defined to be consistent with the Planetocentric coordinate system. Uses linear velocity units for the radius dimension, and angular velocity units for the other two dimensions. The included attributes are not sufficient to identify the endpoints of the vector. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Velocity_Vector_Planetocentric_Generic
class.description: The Velocity_Vector_Planetocentric_Generic is a three dimensional spherical vector (radius, longitude, latitude) with the angular coordinates defined to be consistent with the Planetocentric coordinate system. Uses linear velocity units for the radius dimension, and angular velocity units for the other two dimensions. Includes attributes to identify the endpoints of the vector. While the class Coordinate_System_Identification is optional, it must be used here if the coordinate system has not been specified in the enclosing class.

class.title: Vertical_Vector
class.description: The Vertical_Vector encodes the vertical axis of the image plane (V' or Vp), the coordinate (Vc) of the image row(?) at the optical center of the image plane, and the vertical focal length (Vs) of the camera, in pixels.

class.title: Command_Parameters
class.description: The Command_Parameters class contains attributes used to identify or describe the commands sent to a spacecraft to perform one or more actions resulting in the acquisition of the current data product.

class.title: Data_Correction_File
class.description: The Data_Correction_File class specifies the data correction information to be applied according to other data correction parameters. As a subclass of the Data_Correction_Parameters class, this specifies calibration applied to the science data as opposed to calibration the instrument before launch. As a subclass of the Derived_Product_Parameters class, this specifies a file describing the post processing of the product after radiometric and photometric calibrations. See the Derived_Product_Parameters class for more information.

class.title: Data_Correction_Parameters
class.description: The Data_Correction_Parameters class describes data processing steps applied to data, either on-board a spacecraft or after receipt of the data on the ground, to remove artifacts introduced into the data by the instrument.

class.title: Derived_Product_Parameters
class.description: The Derived_Product_Parameters class contains attributes used to identify and describe post processing performed on products in order to produce a higher level product. The processing performed after radiometric and photometric correction and often cosmetic in nature. For example, filtering, edge matching, seam correction, and blending.

class.title: Downsample_Parameters
class.description: The Downsample_Parameters class contains attributes related to the compression or reduction in resolution of data through sub-sampling.

class.title: Filter
class.description: The Filter class describes the filter associated with a particular observation. The filter may be identified by name, identifier, number or some combination of these.

class.title: Geometric_Correction_Parameters
class.description: The Geometric_Correction_Parameters class identifies and describes stereo partner used to linearize the image including the linearization mode, the FOV, and reference to the stereo partner.

class.title: Imaging_Instrument_Parameters
class.description: The Imaging_Instrument_Parameters class contains attributes providing the values of any dynamic physical or operating characteristics of an instrument.

class.title: Instrument_Compression_Parameters
class.description: The Instrument_Compression_Parameters class contains attributes describing onboard compression parameters.

class.title: Instrument_Compression_Segment
class.description: This class provides attributes describing each segment into which data was partitioned for error containment purposes as part of the compression process.

class.title: Instrument_Device_Temperature
class.description: The Instrument_Device_Temperature class provides a container for the set of temperatures of some point on an instrument or other device.

class.title: Instrument_Device_Temperature_Index
class.description: The Instrument_Device_Temperature_Index class provides the temperature of some point on an instrument or other device.

class.title: Packet_Parameters
class.description: The Packet_Parameters class contains parameters describing the packetized telemetry data.

class.title: Pointing_Correction_Parameters
class.description: The Pointing_Correction_Parameters class contains attributes used to identify and describe the camera model transformations completed in order to update pointing information.

class.title: Pointing_Model_Index
class.description: The Pointing_Model_Index class specifies the name and value (numeric) parameters needed by the pointing model identified by the pointing_model_name attribute in the Pointing_Correction_Parameters parent class. The meaning of any given parameter is defined by the pointing model.

class.title: Process
class.description: The Process class describes an action taken upon a product, typically by a software program.

class.title: Process_Owner
class.description: The Process_Owner class describes the individual and/or organization that made changes to a product.

class.title: Processing_History
class.description: The Processing_History class provides a listing of the programs used to create the current product.

class.title: Product_Identification
class.description: The Product_Identification class contains identifying information to associate the image with other products.

class.title: Radiometric_Correction_Parameters
class.description: The Radiometric_Correction_Parameters class is container for the type and details of the radiometric calibration performed on the product.

class.title: Reference_Pixel_Image
class.description: The Reference_Pixel_Image class specifies the Internal Reference to the IMAGE_ID or PRODUCT_ID for the reference pixel EDR that was used to remove bias in generating the RDR. NOTE: If the model rather than a reference pixel EDR was used to remove the bias then this keyword is not included in the PDS label.

class.title: Software
class.description: The Software class identifies the software program used to make changes to a product.

class.title: Source_Product
class.description: The Source_Product class contains one of the source product reference for this derived product.

class.title: Source_Products
class.description: The Source_Products class contains the source product references for this derived product.

class.title: Stereo_Product_Parameters
class.description: The Stereo_Product_Parameters class identifies and describes stereo partner used to linearize the image.

class.title: Stereo_Product_Reference
class.description: The Stereo_Product_Reference class specifies internal reference to the stereo partner used to linearize the image when linearization_mode is "ACTUAL". This class may be absent if the mode is not "ACTUAL".

class.title: Subframe_Parameters
class.description: The Subframe_Parameters class describes the position and other optional characteristics of an image subframe, relative to the original image.

class.title: Telemetry_Parameters
class.description: The Telemetry_Parameters class contains downlink-related attributes used primarily during mission operations.

class.title: Observation_Information
class.description: The Observation_Information class provides information about a science observation.

class.title: ASCII_AnyURI
class.description: The ASCII AnyURI class indicates a URI or its subclasses URN and URL.

class.title: ASCII_Boolean
class.description: The ASCII_Boolean class indicates a boolean. The allowed values are 'true' and 'false'.

class.title: ASCII_DOI
class.description: The ASCII DOI class indicates a digital object identifier (DOI).

class.title: ASCII_Date
class.description: The ASCII_Date class indicates a date in either YMD or DOY format.

class.title: ASCII_Date_DOY
class.description: The ASCII_Date_DOY class indicates a date in DOY format.

class.title: ASCII_Date_Time
class.description: The ASCII_Date_Time class indicates a date in either YMD or DOY format and time.

class.title: ASCII_Date_Time_DOY
class.description: The ASCII_Date_Time_DOY class indicates a date in DOY format and time.

class.title: ASCII_Date_Time_DOY_UTC
class.description: The ASCII_Date_Time_DOY_UTC class indicates a date (in DOY format) and time in UTC.

class.title: ASCII_Date_Time_UTC
class.description: The ASCII_Date_Time_UTC class indicates a date and time in UTC format.

class.title: ASCII_Date_Time_YMD
class.description: The ASCII_Date_Time_YMD class indicates a date in YMD format and time.

class.title: ASCII_Date_Time_YMD_UTC
class.description: The ASCII_Date_Time_YMD_UTC class indicates a date (in YMD format) and time in UTC.

class.title: ASCII_Date_YMD
class.description: The ASCII_Date_YMD class indicates a date in YMD format.

class.title: ASCII_Directory_Path_Name
class.description: The ASCII Directory Path Name class indicates a system directory path.

class.title: ASCII_File_Name
class.description: The ASCII File Name class indicates a system file name.

class.title: ASCII_File_Specification_Name
class.description: The ASCII File Specification Name class indicates a system file including directory path, file name, and file extension.

class.title: ASCII_Integer
class.description: The ASCII_Integer class indicates an integer.

class.title: ASCII_LID
class.description: The ASCII_LID class indicates a logical identifier.

class.title: ASCII_LIDVID
class.description: The ASCII_LIDVID class indicates a logical identifier and version identifier.

class.title: ASCII_LIDVID_LID
class.description: The ASCII_LIDVID_LID class indicates a logical identifier and version identifier or simply the logical identfier.

class.title: ASCII_MD5_Checksum
class.description: The ASCII MD5 Checksum class indicates a checksum computed by the Message-Digest algorithm 5 (MD5).

class.title: ASCII_NonNegative_Integer
class.description: The ASCII_NonNegative_Integer class indicates a non-negative  integer.

class.title: ASCII_Numeric_Base16
class.description: The ASCII Numeric Base16 class indicates a ASCII encoded string constrained to hexadecimal digits.

class.title: ASCII_Numeric_Base2
class.description: The ASCII Numeric Base2 class indicates a ASCII encoded string constrained to binary digits.

class.title: ASCII_Numeric_Base8
class.description: The ASCII Numeric Base8 class indicates a ASCII encoded string constrained to octal digits.

class.title: ASCII_Real
class.description: The ASCII_Real class indicates a real.

class.title: ASCII_Short_String_Collapsed
class.description: The ASCII_Short_String_Collapsed class indicates a limited length, whitespace-collapsed string.

class.title: ASCII_Short_String_Preserved
class.description: The ASCII_Short_String_Preserved class indicates a limited length, whitespace-preserved string.

class.title: ASCII_String
class.description: The ASCII_String class indicates a limited length ASCII text string with whitespaces removed.

class.title: ASCII_Text_Collapsed
class.description: The ASCII_Text_Collapsed class indicates an unlimited length, whitespace-collapsed text string.

class.title: ASCII_Text_Preserved
class.description: The ASCII_Text_Preserved class indicates an unlimited length, whitespace-preserved text string.

class.title: ASCII_Time
class.description: The ASCII_Time class indicates a time value.

class.title: ASCII_VID
class.description: The ASCII_VID class indicates a version identifier.

class.title: Agency
class.description: The Agency class provides a description of an entity that provides regional or national level governance over nodes within the federated Planetary Data System.

class.title: Aggregation_Object
class.description: The Aggregation Object class defines a Conceptual Object that is used to aggregate other objects.

class.title: Alias
class.description: The Alias class provides a single alternate name and identification for this product in this or some other archive or data system.

class.title: Alias_List
class.description: The Alias_List class provides a list of paired alternate names and identifications for this product in this or some other archive or data system.

class.title: Ancillary_Object
class.description: The Ancillary Object defines a Supplemental Object that cannot reasonably be classified as any other Supplemental Object.

class.title: Archival_Information_Package
class.description: The Archival Information Package (AIP) class defines an Information Package consisting of the Content Information and the associated Preservation Description Information (PDI), which is preserved within an archive that conforms to the Open Archive Information System (OAIS) Reference Model.

class.title: Archive_Support_Object
class.description: The Archive Support defines a Supplemental Object that is used by the system for an archive function.

class.title: Array
class.description: The Array class defines a homogeneous N-dimensional array of scalars. The Array class is the parent class for all n-dimensional arrays of scalars.

class.title: Array_1D
class.description: The Array 1D class is the parent class for all one dimensional array based classes.

class.title: Array_2D
class.description: The Array 2D class is the parent class for all two dimensional array based classes.

class.title: Array_2D_Image
class.description: The Array 2D Image class is an extension of the Array 2D class and defines a two dimensional image.

class.title: Array_2D_Map
class.description: The Array 2D Map class is an extension of the Array 2D class and defines a  two dimensional map.

class.title: Array_2D_Spectrum
class.description: The Array 2D Spectrum class is an extension of the Array 2D class and defines a  two dimensional spectrum.

class.title: Array_3D
class.description: The Array 3D class is the parent class for all three dimensional array based classes.

class.title: Array_3D_Image
class.description: The Array 3D Image class is an extension of the Array 3D class and defines a  three dimensional image.

class.title: Array_3D_Movie
class.description: The Array 3D  Movie class is an extension of the Array 3D class and defines a  movie as a set of two dimensional images in a time series.

class.title: Array_3D_Spectrum
class.description: The Array 3D Spectrum class is an extension of the Array 3D class and defines a  three dimensional spectrum.

class.title: Axis_Array
class.description: The Axis Array class is used as a component of the array class and defines an axis of the array.

class.title: Band_Bin
class.description: The Band_Bin class specifies the characteristics of an individual spectral band in a spectral qube.

class.title: Band_Bin_Set
class.description: The Band_Bin_Set class contains the spectral characteristics for all the spectral bands in a qube.

class.title: Binary_Data_Type
class.description: The Binary Data Type class is the abstract parent class for binary data types found in the digital objects.

class.title: Bundle
class.description: The Bundle class describes a collection of collections.

class.title: Bundle_Member_Entry
class.description: The Bundle Member Entry class provides a member reference to a collection.

class.title: Byte_Stream
class.description: The Byte Stream class defines a stream of bytes.

class.title: Character_Data_Type
class.description: The Character Data Type class is the parent class for data types used to classify the values of attributes in class descriptions, i.e., product labels and character digital objects.

class.title: Checksum_Manifest
class.description: The Checksum_Manifest class defines a two column table for file references and checksums.

class.title: Citation_Information
class.description: The Citation_Information class provides specific fields often used in citing the product in journal articles, abstract services, and other reference contexts.

class.title: Collection
class.description: The Collection class provides a description of a set of products.

class.title: Complex
class.description: Complex Binary Data Types

class.title: ComplexLSB16
class.description: Complex number consisting of two LSB 8 byte decimal reals.

class.title: ComplexLSB8
class.description: Complex number consisting of two LSB 4 byte decimal reals.

class.title: ComplexMSB16
class.description: Complex number consisting of two MSB 8 byte decimal reals.

class.title: ComplexMSB8
class.description: Complex number consisting of two MSB 4 byte decimal reals.

class.title: Conceptual_Context_Object
class.description: The Conceptual Context Object class defines a Conceptual Object that is used to provide contextual information for an Observational Object.

class.title: Conceptual_Object
class.description: The Conceptual Object class defines a non-tangible object that is also not a digital object.

class.title: Context_Area
class.description: The Context Area provides context information for a product.

class.title: DD_Association
class.description: The DD_Association class defines the association between two classes or a class and an attribute in a data dictionary.

class.title: DD_Association_External
class.description: The DD_Association_External class defines the association between classes and attributes within the local data dictionary and those external to the local data dictionary.

class.title: DD_Attribute
class.description: The DD_Attribute class defines an attribute for a data dictionary.

class.title: DD_Attribute_Full
class.description: The DD_Attribute_Full class provides a more complete definition of an attribute in the data dictionary.

class.title: DD_Attribute_Reference
class.description: The DD Attribute Reference class provides a reference to an attribute using a namespace identifier and the attribute name.

class.title: DD_Class
class.description: The DD_Class class defines a class for a data dictionary.

class.title: DD_Class_Full
class.description: The DD_Class_Full class provides a more complete definition of a class for a data dictionary.

class.title: DD_Class_Reference
class.description: The DD Class Reference class provides a reference to a class using a namespace identifier and the class name.

class.title: DD_Permissible_Value
class.description: The DD_Permissible_Value class lists permissible values and their meanings.

class.title: DD_Permissible_Value_Full
class.description: The DD_Permissible_Value_Full class lists permissible values, their meanings, and the dates when active.

class.title: DD_Rule
class.description: The DD_Rule class defines a Schematron rule for a data dictionary.

class.title: DD_Rule_Statement
class.description: The DD_Rule_Statement class defines a Schematron rule statement.

class.title: DD_Value_Domain
class.description: The DD_Value_Domain class defines an attribute's permissible values and their constraints.

class.title: DD_Value_Domain_Full
class.description: The DD_Value_Domain_Full class provides a more complete definition of a attribute's value domain.

class.title: DIP_Deep_Archive
class.description: The Dissemination Information Package Deep Archive class is an Information Package derived from one or more AIPs and is received by the National Space Science Data Center (NSSDC).

class.title: Data_Object
class.description: The Data Object class defines a thing about which almost nothing is known.

class.title: Data_Type
class.description: The Data Type class is the abstract parent class for several classes of data types.

class.title: Decimal_Integer
class.description: Decimal Integer Binary Data Types

class.title: Decimal_Real
class.description: Floating Point Binary Data Types

class.title: Digital_Object
class.description: The Digital Object class defines a sequence of digital bits.

class.title: Discipline_Area
class.description: The Discipline area allows the insertion of discipline specific metadata.

class.title: Discipline_Facets
class.description: The Discipline_Facets class contains the discipline-related search facets.  It is required and may not be repeated. Note that Science_Facets was modeled with Discipline_Facets as a component and Discipline_Facets was modeled with Group_Facet1 and Group_Facet2 as components. This dependency hierarchy was flattened and only Science_Facets exists in the schema.

class.title: Display_2D_Image
class.description: The Display_2D_Image class provides attributes to enable the display of a 2 dimensional image.

class.title: Dissemination_Information_Package
class.description: The Dissemination Information Package (DIP) class defines an Information Package, derived from one or more AIPs, that is received by a consumer.

class.title: Document
class.description: The Document class describes a document.

class.title: Document_Edition
class.description: A Document Edition is one complete version of the document in a set of files that is distinguished by language, a unique assemblage of file formats, or some other criteria.

class.title: Document_File
class.description: The Document File class describes a file which is a part of a document.

class.title: Document_Object
class.description: The Document Object defines a Supplemental Object that provides readable evidence for humans.

class.title: Element_Array
class.description: The Element Array class is used as a component of the array class and defines an element of the array.

class.title: Encoded_Binary
class.description: The Encoded Binary class describes a binary encoded byte stream. This class is used to describe files in the repository that are being registered using  Product_File_Repository.

class.title: Encoded_Byte_Stream
class.description: The Encoded Byte Stream class defines byte streams that must be decoded by software before use. These byte streams must only use standard encodings. The Encoded Byte Stream class is the parent class for all encoded byte streams.

class.title: Encoded_Header
class.description: The Encoded Header class describes a header that has been encoded using an encoding scheme that is compliant to an external standard.

class.title: Encoded_Image
class.description: The Encoded Image class is used for ancillary images in standard formats, such as JPEG.

class.title: Encoded_Native
class.description: The Encoded Native class describes a binary encoded byte stream. This class is used to describe data objects for Product_Native.

class.title: External_Reference
class.description: The External_Reference class is used to reference a source outside the PDS registry system.

class.title: External_Reference_Extended
class.description: The External_Reference_Extended class is used to reference a source outside the PDS registry system. This extension is used in the local data dictionary.

class.title: Facility
class.description: The Facility class provides a name and address for a  terrestrial observatory or laboratory.

class.title: Field
class.description: The Field class defines a field of a record and is the parent class of all specific field classes.The Field class defines a field of a record or a field of a group and is the parent class of all specific field classes.

class.title: Field_Binary
class.description: The Field_Binary class defines a field of a binary record or a field of a binary group.

class.title: Field_Bit
class.description: The Field_Bit class provides parameters for extracting one field out of a string of bytes which contains packed data (that is, data values either smaller than a single byte, or crossing byte boundaries, or both.

class.title: Field_Character
class.description: The Field_Character class defines a field of a character record or a field of a character group.

class.title: Field_Delimited
class.description: The Field_Delimited class defines a field of a delimited record or a field of a delimited group.

class.title: Field_Statistics
class.description: The Field Statistics class provides a set of metrics for a column formed by a field in a repeating record.

class.title: File
class.description: The File class consists of attributes that describe a file in a data store.

class.title: File_Area
class.description: The File_Area class defines a File and its component data objects.

class.title: File_Area_Ancillary
class.description: The File Area Ancillary class describes a file and one or more tagged_data_objects contained within the file.

class.title: File_Area_Binary
class.description: The File Area Binary class describes a file that contains an encoded byte stream.

class.title: File_Area_Browse
class.description: The File Area Browse class describes a file and one or more tagged_data_objects contained within the file.

class.title: File_Area_Checksum_Manifest
class.description: The File Area Checksum Manifest class describes a file that contains a two column table for file references and checksums.

class.title: File_Area_Encoded_Image
class.description: The File Area Encoded Image class describes a file that contains an Encoded Image object.

class.title: File_Area_Inventory
class.description: The File Area Inventory class describes a file and an inventory consisting of references to  members.

class.title: File_Area_Native
class.description: The File Area Native describes tagged_data_objects collected from an instrument.

class.title: File_Area_Observational
class.description: The File Area Observational class describes, for an observational product, a file and one or more tagged_data_objects contained within the file.

class.title: File_Area_Observational_Supplemental
class.description: The File Area Observational Supplemental class describes, for an observational product, additional files and tagged_data_objects contained within the file.

class.title: File_Area_SIP_Deep_Archive
class.description: The File Area SIP Deep Archive class describes the File Area for the Submission Information Package (SIP) for the NASA planetary science deep archive.

class.title: File_Area_SPICE_Kernel
class.description: The File Area SPICE Kernel class describes a file that contains a SPICE Kernel object.

class.title: File_Area_Service_Description
class.description: The File Area Service Description class describes a file that contains a service description.

class.title: File_Area_Text
class.description: The File Area Text class describes a file that contains a text stream object.

class.title: File_Area_Transfer_Manifest
class.description: The File Area Transfer Manifest class describes a file that contains a two column table that maps the logical identifiers and version ids of products to their file specification names.

class.title: File_Area_Update
class.description: The File Area Update class is a File Area that describes a file that contains one or  more digital objects used to provide additional metadata for registered products.

class.title: File_Area_XML_Schema
class.description: The File Area XML Schema class describes a file that contains a resource used for the PDS4 implementation into XML.

class.title: Finding_Aid_Object
class.description: The Finding Aid Object defines a Supplemental Object that supports a user when attempting to locate data.

class.title: Geometry_Group
class.description: The Geometry Group class groups geometry information.

class.title: Group

attribute.title: blue_channel_band
attribute.description: The blue_channel_band attribute identifies the number of the band, along the band axis, that should be loaded, by default, into the blue channel of a display device. The first band along the band axis has band number 1.

attribute.title: color_display_axis
attribute.description: The color_display_axis attribute identifies, by name, the axis of an Array (or Array subclass) that is intended to be displayed in the color dimension of a display device. I.e., bands from this dimension will be loaded into the red, green, and blue bands of the display device. The value of this attribute must match the value of one, and only one, axis_name attribute in an Axis_Array class of the associated Array.

attribute.title: green_channel_band
attribute.description: The green_channel_band attribute identifies the number of the band, along the band axis, that should be loaded, by default, into the green channel of a display device. The first band along the band axis has band number 1.

attribute.title: red_channel_band
attribute.description: The red_channel_band attribute identifies the number of the band, along the band axis, that should be loaded, by default, into the red channel of a display device. The first band along the band axis has band number 1.

attribute.title: comment
attribute.description: The comment attribute is a character string expressing one or more remarks or thoughts relevant to the object.

attribute.title: horizontal_display_axis
attribute.description: The horizontal_display_axis attribute identifies, by name, the axis of an Array (or Array subclass) that is intended to be displayed in the horizontal or "sample" dimension on a display device. The value of this attribute must match the value of one, and only one, axis_name attribute in an Axis_Array class of the associated Array.

attribute.title: horizontal_display_direction
attribute.description: The horizontal_display_direction attribute specifies the direction across the screen of a display device that data along the horizontal axis of an Array is supposed to be displayed.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The lowest indexed element along an array axis should be displayed at the left edge of a display device and elements with higher indices should be displayed further to the right.  Note that this is the standard display direction for most major image formats.

The lowest indexed element along an array axis should be displayed at the right edge of a display device and elements with higher indices should be displayed further to the left.  Note that virtually no image display formats use this display direction.  Use this only when deliberately mirroring the image around the vertical axis.

attribute.title: vertical_display_axis
attribute.description: The vertical_display_axis attribute identifies, by name, the axis of an Array (or Array subclass) that is intended to be displayed in the vertical or "line" dimension on a display device. The value of this attribute must match the value of one, and only one, axis_name attribute in an Axis_Array class of the associated Array.

attribute.title: vertical_display_direction
attribute.description: The vertical_display_direction attribute specifies the direction along the screen of a display device that data along the vertical axis of an Array is supposed to be displayed.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The lowest indexed element along an array axis should be displayed at the bottom edge of a display device and elements with higher indices should be displayed higher up.  This is the display direction typically used for FITS formatted data.

The lowest indexed element along an array axis should be displayed at the top edge of a display device and elements with higher indices should be displayed lower down.  This is the display direction typically used for VICAR formatted data.

attribute.title: comment
attribute.description: The comment attribute is a character string expressing one or more remarks or thoughts relevant to the object.

attribute.title: frame_rate
attribute.description: The frame_rate attribute indicates the number of still pictures (or frames) that should be displayed per unit of time in a video. Note this is NOT necessarily the same as the rate at which the images were acquired.

attribute.title: loop_back_and_forth_flag
attribute.description: The loop_back_and_forth_flag attribute specifies whether or not a movie should only be "looped" or played repeatedly in the forward direction, or whether it should be played forward followed by played in reverse, iteratively.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: When looping, the movie should only be played in the forward direction.  This is the default behavior.
When looping, the movie should be played in the forward direction, followed by the reverse direction, iteratively.

attribute.title: loop_count
attribute.description: The loop_count attribute specifies the number of times a movie should be "looped" or replayed before stopping.

attribute.title: loop_delay
attribute.description: The loop_delay attribute specifies the amount of time to pause between "loops" or repeated playbacks of a movie.
attribute.unitId: day, hr, julian day, microseconds, min, ms, s, yr

attribute.title: loop_flag
attribute.description: The loop_flag attribute specifies whether or not a movie object should be played repeatedly without prompting from the user.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The movie should be not be 'looped' or played repeatedly.
The movie should be 'looped' or played repeatedly.

attribute.title: time_display_axis
attribute.description: The time_display_axis attribute identifies, by name, the axis of an Array (or Array subclass), the bands of which are intended to be displayed sequentially in time on a display device. The frame_rate attribute, if present, provides the rate at which these bands are to be displayed.

attribute.title: comment
attribute.description: The comment attribute is a character string expressing one or more remarks or thoughts relevant to the object.

attribute.title: x_acceleration
attribute.description: The x component of a Cartesian acceleration vector.

attribute.title: y_acceleration
attribute.description: The y component of a Cartesian acceleration vector.

attribute.title: z_acceleration
attribute.description: The z component of a Cartesian acceleration vector.

attribute.title: light_time_correction_applied
attribute.description: The light_time_correction_applied indicates whether or not light travel time correction and stellar aberration correction were used when calculating the values in the enclosing class. The attribute is nillable with nill_reason = unknown, but only for migrated data. Note: generally, received light travel time is calculated unless a transmitter (e.g., radar, radio)was involved in which the calculation typically is transmitted light time.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning:
Neither light travel time nor stellar aberration was used when

attribute.title: device_id
attribute.description: The device_id attribute specifies the abbreviated identification of an articulation device.

attribute.title: device_mode
attribute.description: The device_mode attribute specifies the deployment state (i.e., physical configuration) of an articulation device at the time of data acquisition. Examples include arm vibe, deployed, free space, stowed.

attribute.title: device_name
attribute.description: The device_name attribute specifies the common name of an articulation device.

attribute.title: device_phase
attribute.description: The device_phase attribute specifies the current phase of the mission, from an articulation-device-centric point of view.

attribute.title: name
attribute.description: The name attribute provides a word or combination of words by which the object is known.

attribute.title: cahvore_model_parameter
attribute.description: The cahvore_parameter_type attribute is a scalar floating-point number used for CAHVORE Type 3 models (see cahvore_model_type). If the parameter is 1.0, the model is identical to type 1; if 0.0, it is identical to type 2. Most fish-eye lenses use a value in between. See the references.

attribute.title: cahvore_model_type
attribute.description: The cahvore_model_type attribute indicates which variant of the CAHVORE model to use. Type 1 is a perspective-projection model, similar to CAHV and CAHVOR except for the moving entrance pupil. Type 2 is a fish-eye lens model reflecting fundamentally different geometry. Type 3 is a generalization that includes the first two, and is used for most fisheye-type lenses (see cahvore_model_parameter).

          CAHVOR except for the moving entrance pupil
